          <a href="https://twitter.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">X</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="form-section">
      <h2>Customer booking / feedback form</h2>
      <p>Users submit booking requests or feedback. The form will generate an email message (visible below) you can send via your default mail client. No database involved.</p>

      <form id="bookingForm" class="form-grid" onsubmit="return false;" novalidate>
        <label>
          <span>Name</span>
          <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required placeholder="Your full name">
        </label>

        <label>
          <span>Email</span>
          <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required placeholder="you@example.com">
        </label>

        <label>
          <span>Type</span>
          <select id="type" name="type">
            <option>Booking request</option>
            <option>Feedback</option>
            <option>General question</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label class="full">
          <span>Details</span>
          <textarea id="details" name="details" rows="4" placeholder="Tell us your booking / feedback details"></textarea>
        </label>

        <div class="form-actions full">
          <button id="previewBtn" class="btn">Preview email</button>
          <button id="sendBtn" class="btn ghost" type="button">Open in Mail</button>
        </div>

        <div class="full">
          <h3>Generated email preview</h3>
          <pre id="emailPreview" class="email-preview">No preview yet — fill the form and click "Preview email".</pre>
        </div>
      </form>
    </section>

    <section class="design-explain">
      <h2>Design explanation</h2>
      <p>The page focuses on conversion: quick contact + clear call-to-action. Social links are included for continuity between the website and marketing channels. The form uses client-side validation and generates a <code>mailto:</code> link as a simple, testable mechanism for sending the captured info to restaurant staff.</p>
